the spaces between these parts.\r\nWithout the spaces, your ideas sound like a train wreck of jumbled thoughts.\r\n\r\n<strong>Get comfortable with silence!</strong>\r\nToo many business presenters come across as rushed when they speak. So, get comfortable with silence when you speak in public!\r\nOf course, you can go too far. Some politicians have long gaps after every sentence. (They do it to define the sound bites they want the media to repeat, but this needs to be balanced with natural speech to connect with an audience).\r\nSo, chunk your explanations. The gaps will help you relax and fully engage your listeners.\r\nBe Sociable, Share!','Focus on the gaps, not just your words','I recently attended a conference where two of the speakers raced through their talk without pausing.\r\nIt was so exhausting.\r\nAnd their ideas seemed less important with the speaker racing through them.','inherit','open','open','','298-revision-4','','','2013-03-26 17:12:53','2013-03-26 09:12:53','',298,'http://hanxianlong.tk/?p=304',0,'revision','',0),(305,1,'2013-03-26 17:14:23','2013-03-26 09:14:23','<strong>Focus on the gaps, not just your words </strong>December 28, 2011 By cam Leave a Comment\n<div><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.jobexcel.com/uploads/allimg/130314/1_1321435352.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"288\" border=\"0\" /></div>\nI recently attended a conference where two of the speakers raced through their talk without pausing.\nIt was so exhausting.\nAnd their ideas seemed less important with the speaker racing through them.\n\n<strong>We all crave a START and/or an END:</strong>\nThe human mind responds instinctively to the start or the end of anything so when the gaps are highlighted, you define the end of one section and the start of another. This automatically engages your audience.\nThere are benefits all round:\n<strong>For the listener:</strong> It’s easier to process your ideas and they feel more comfortable asking questions.\n<strong>For the speaker:</strong> Gaps give you the space to think clearly — to observe the audience or listen to the other person, to breathe, to be unhurried and genuine.\n\n<strong>Public Speaking tip:</strong>\nExperiment with directing your attention to the gaps. What does that mean?\nMusic is defined by the spaces between the notes. In the same way, ideas and explanations should be broken into chunks/sections/blocks/pieces/components/chapters/parts…\n…and the gaps are the spaces between these parts.\nWithout the spaces, your ideas sound like a train wreck of jumbled thoughts.\n\n<strong>Get comfortable with silence!</strong>\nToo many business presenters come across as rushed when they speak. So, get comfortable with silence when you speak in public!\nOf course, you can go too far. Some politicians have long gaps after every sentence. (They do it to define the sound bites they want the media to repeat, but this needs to be balanced with natural speech to connect with an audience).\nSo, chunk your explanations. The gaps will help you relax and fully engage your listeners.\nBe Sociable, Share!','Focus on the gaps, not just your words','I recently attended a conference where two of the speakers raced through their talk without pausing.It was so exhausting.And their ideas seemed less important with the speaker racing through them.','inherit','open','open','','298-autosave','','','2013-03-26 17:14:23','2013-03-26 09:14:23','',298,'http://hanxianlong.tk/?p=305',0,'revision','',0),(306,1,'2013-03-14 13:27:59','2013-03-14 05:27:59','<strong>The Daily Show: The power of Chunking</strong>\r\nDecember 29, 2011 By cam Leave a Comment \r\n\r\n<div><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.jobexcel.com/uploads/allimg/130314/1_1321437601.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"288\" border=\"0\" />\r\n</div>\r\n\r\nThe July 28 episode of the Daily Show with Jon Stewart had author Peter Tomsen talking about his 900 page(!) book “The Wars of Afghanistan”.\r\nThroughout, he summarized his key points using elements of Chunk Theory – for example, the numbering of points before explaining them.\r\nIn response to one question, he said “there are two reasons…” which he explained. BUT, then said “Finally…” and attempted to add another reason.\r\n \r\n<strong>I’m sorry, you said 2 things not 3</strong>\r\nThe host, John Stewart, stopped him cold: “I’m sorry, you said 2 things…”\r\nThey joked about that for a while and Jon allowed him to share his third point.\r\nBut the issue here is that ‘speaking in chunks‘ – in this case outlining the number of points you will make before you make them – is a technique that is engaging enough to keep the full attention of your listener.\r\nThis simple but powerful approach virtually forces people to give you time to address each point. We can’t help it. We literally process information in ‘chunks’ so it always seems reasonable to listen to (and check off) numbered points. The details might be overwhelming, but breaking it into chunks keeps people on board.\r\n \r\n<strong>Flout this principle at your own peril</strong>\r\nIt’s power is highlighted when you abuse it.\r\nThe listener is primed for (in this case) 2 chunks, so when you violate your own principle and attempt 3 chunks, it feels so noticeable, so glaring, so conspicuous. We can’t let slide such a flagrant breach of the structure laid out for the conversation.\r\nThis just shows how irresistible the chunked ‘conversation structure’ can be to an audience.\r\nBe Sociable, Share！\r\n','The Daily Show: The power of Chunking','','inherit','open','open','','296-revision-2','','','2013-03-14 13:27:59','2013-03-14 05:27:59','',296,'http://hanxianlong.tk/?p=306',0,'revision','',0),(307,1,'2013-02-25 16:46:49','2013-02-25 08:46:49','一、 叱咤商场、官场、战场（只限于战争时期），运筹帷幄，一呼百应。无论外表高矮胖瘦，让所有的女人敬而仰之。\r\n\r\n二、 目标坚定，百折不挠，宠辱不惊。处于劣势时能够卧薪尝胆，十年磨一剑，忍住寂寞，积蓄隐蔽的实力；处于优势时保持低调，时刻警惕“枪打出头鸟”的子弹。总之，熊市时把自己经营成一支升值的潜力股，牛市时具有防止缩水的意识和能力。\r\n\r\n三、 会用钱。有钱不会花等于没钱。有钱的目的是可以用来做想做的事情。为健康、快乐、见识、友谊、人情花钱叫投资，因为可以为你换来更多的幸福感。既然是投资就要计算投入产出，能够以少的投入获取更大回报的才叫把钱用在刀刃上。\r\n\r\n四、 慧眼识人。人行走在江湖，就是在茫茫人海中游弋，近至妻儿、父母、兄弟姐妹，远到同学、同事、朋友、客户、一面之交之人、陌路相逢擦肩而过之人。世上所有人都有利己和利他的两面性，明白了这一点，就知道为什么对再亲的人你也没有必要把自己焚烧去满足他，就知道即使是对一个陌路人也可以赠送一个微笑，赠人玫瑰手有余香。世上的人都在利己和利他的两重境界游走，有一双识人的慧眼，就能够把握好利己和利他的度，与任何人都保持着合适的距离。\r\n\r\n五、 在危机慌乱中冷静如冰，沉着如山，是所有人眼中的主心骨。\r\n\r\n六、 在人情场中，热情似火，豪情万丈。对妻子柔情似水，对儿女呵护备至，对亲人关爱有加，对朋友仗义豪情，让生活因你而美好。\r\n\r\n七、 有浪漫的情怀。是否拥有诗情画意与生活条件无关，没钱游山玩水，一样可以赏路边的小草野花，听雨听风看雪花飘落，心中自有一份美好的情愫。拥有浪漫情怀的人即使在一穷二白，举目无亲的时候也不会灭绝生的希望，它是滋养你灵魂的一剂药方，是生命的火种，能让你起死回生。\r\n\r\n八、信守诺言。借银行的贷款永远不拖欠，高信用值是衡量你价值的一部分。对朋友对同事、上司、下属、客户的承诺一言九鼎，所以不要轻易许诺，一旦承诺就要兑现。对女人最容易许下承诺，其实未来是个未知数，没有谁能保证什么，只要让她相信你会尽最大的努力给她你能给予的最好的就可以了。一旦失信于一个女人就相当于她心中的一座山塌了，很难重建的。','一流成功男人要具备的八大特征','','inherit','open','open','','227-revision-3','','','2013-02-25 16:46:49','2013-02-25 08:46:49','',227,'http://hanxianlong.tk/?p=307',0,'revision','',0),(308,1,'2013-03-26 17:15:59','2013-03-26 09:15:59','一、 叱咤商场、官场、战场（只限于战争时期），运筹帷幄，一呼百应。无论外表高矮胖瘦，让所有的女人敬而仰之。\r\n\r\n二、 目标坚定，百折不挠，宠辱不惊。处于劣势时能够卧薪尝胆，十年磨一剑，忍住寂寞，积蓄隐蔽的实力；处于优势时保持低调，时刻警惕“枪打出头鸟”的子弹。总之，熊市时把自己经营成一支升值的潜力股，牛市时具有防止缩水的意识和能力。\r\n\r\n三、 会用钱。有钱不会花等于没钱。有钱的目的是可以用来做想做的事情。为健康、快乐、见识、友谊、人情花钱叫投资，因为可以为你换来更多的幸福感。既然是投资就要计算投入产出，能够以少的投入获取更大回报的才叫把钱用在刀刃上。\r\n\r\n四、 慧眼识人。人行走在江湖，就是在茫茫人海中游弋，近至妻儿、父母、兄弟姐妹，远到同学、同事、朋友、客户、一面之交之人、陌路相逢擦肩而过之人。世上所有人都有利己和利他的两面性，明白了这一点，就知道为什么对再亲的人你也没有必要把自己焚烧去满足他，就知道即使是对一个陌路人也可以赠送一个微笑，赠人玫瑰手有余香。世上的人都在利己和利他的两重境界游走，有一双识人的慧眼，就能够把握好利己和利他的度，与任何人都保持着合适的距离。\r\n\r\n五、 在危机慌乱中冷静如冰，沉着如山，是所有人眼中的主心骨。\r\n\r\n六、 在人情场中，热情似火，豪情万丈。对妻子柔情似水，对儿女呵护备至，对亲人关爱有加，对朋友仗义豪情，让生活因你而美好。\r\n\r\n七、 有浪漫的情怀。是否拥有诗情画意与生活条件无关，没钱游山玩水，一样可以赏路边的小草野花，听雨听风看雪花飘落，心中自有一份美好的情愫。拥有浪漫情怀的人即使在一穷二白，举目无亲的时候也不会灭绝生的希望，它是滋养你灵魂的一剂药方，是生命的火种，能让你起死回生。\r\n\r\n八、信守诺言。借银行的贷款永远不拖欠，高信用值是衡量你价值的一部分。对朋友对同事、上司、下属、客户的承诺一言九鼎，所以不要轻易许诺，一旦承诺就要兑现。对女人最容易许下承诺，其实未来是个未知数，没有谁能保证什么，只要让她相信你会尽最大的努力给她你能给予的最好的就可以了。一旦失信于一个女人就相当于她心中的一座山塌了，很难重建的。','一流成功男人要具备的八大特征',' 叱咤商场、官场、战场（只限于战争时期），运筹帷幄，一呼百应。无论外表高矮胖瘦，让所有的女人敬而仰之。 目标坚定，百折不挠，宠辱不惊。处于劣势时能够卧薪尝胆，十年磨一剑，忍住寂寞，积蓄隐蔽的实力；处于优势时保持低调，时刻警惕“枪打出头鸟”的子弹。总之，熊市时把自己经营成一支升值的潜力股，牛市时具有防止缩水的意识和能力。','inherit','open','open','','227-revision-4','','','2013-03-26 17:15:59','2013-03-26 09:15:59','',227,'http://hanxianlong.tk/?p=308',0,'revision','',0),(309,1,'2013-03-14 13:20:25','2013-03-14 05:20:25','Barriers to communication: “Not about winning”\r\nJanuary 9, 2012 By cam Leave a Comment \r\n<div><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.jobexcel.com/uploads/allimg/130314/1_1228402825.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"288\" border=\"0\" />\r\n</div>\r\nI recently went to a school sports day for 6 to 10 year olds.\r\nThe teacher introducing the event delivered the message<strong> ‘It’s not about winning, it’s about having fun‘.</strong>\r\n \r\nUnfortunately it’s a lie.\r\n \r\nThis message is just not accurate. And it stifles everyone’s communication skills. Every kid would like to win. Every parent at the event would like their child to win. The winner gets more satisfaction and glory. In fact, if it wasn’t about winning, there would be no race!\r\nWe deliver messages like this because we want to spare our children the cut throat pressure that may go with competition. A noble goal. But a goal that won’t be achieved if the children don’t believe what we say.\r\nHowever, we can easily create a true and accurate message that breaks down the barrier and achieves the intended goal; with just a slight tweak.\r\n \r\n‘It’s not just about winning, it’s also about having fun’.\r\n \r\nBecause this message states the truth, the audience is still listening to the important point about having fun. This message introduces the day and sets the right tone.\r\nA true message resonates and creates clear communication. A false message is treated with disdain and encourages duplicity.\r\nIt’s the same for clear business communication. You can improve your communication skills by modifying your messages.\r\nWe don’t have to be fake, we just need to think clearly about how the message is received.\r\nBe Sociable, Share!\r\n','Barriers to communication: “Not about winning”','','inherit','open','open','','294-revision-2','','','2013-03-14 13:20:25','2013-03-14 05:20:25','',294,'http://hanxianlong.tk/?p=309',0,'revision','',0),(310,1,'2013-03-26 17:16:52','2013-03-26 09:16:52','Barriers to communication: “Not about winning”\r\nJanuary 9, 2012 By cam Leave a Comment\r\n<div><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.jobexcel.com/uploads/allimg/130314/1_1228402825.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"288\" border=\"0\" /></div>\r\nI recently went to a school sports day for 6 to 10 year olds.\r\nThe teacher introducing the event delivered the message<strong> ‘It’s not about winning, it’s about having fun‘.</strong>\r\n\r\nUnfortunately it’s a lie.\r\n\r\nThis message is just not accurate. And it stifles everyone’s communication skills. Every kid would like to win. Every parent at the event would like their child to win. The winner gets more satisfaction and glory. In fact, if it wasn’t about winning, there would be no race!\r\nWe deliver messages like this because we want to spare our children the cut throat pressure that may go with competition. A noble goal. But a goal that won’t be achieved if the children don’t believe what we say.\r\nHowever, we can easily create a true and accurate message that breaks down the barrier and achieves the intended goal; with just a slight tweak.\r\n\r\n‘It’s not just about winning, it’s also about having fun’.\r\n\r\nBecause this message states the truth, the audience is still listening to the important point about having fun. This message introduces the day and sets the right tone.\r\nA true message resonates and creates clear communication. A false message is treated with disdain and encourages duplicity.\r\nIt’s the same for clear business communication. You can improve your communication skills by modifying your messages.\r\nWe don’t have to be fake, we just need to think clearly about how the message is received.\r\nBe Sociable, Share!','Barriers to communication: “Not about winning”','This message is just not accurate. And it stifles everyone’s communication skills. Every kid would like to win. Every parent at the event would like their child to win. The winner gets more satisfaction and glory. In fact, if it wasn’t about winning, there would be no race!\r\nWe deliver messages like this because we want to spare our children the cut throat pressure that may go with competition. A noble goal. But a goal that won’t be achieved if the children don’t believe what we say.\r\nHowever, we can easily create a true and accurate message that breaks down the barrier and achieves the intended goal; with just a slight tweak.','inherit','open','open','','294-revision-3','','','2013-03-26 17:16:52','2013-03-26 09:16:52','',294,'http://hanxianlong.tk/?p=310',0,'revision','',0),(311,1,'2013-03-26 17:18:32','2013-03-26 09:18:32','Barriers to communication: “Not about winning”\nJanuary 9, 2012 By cam Leave a Comment\n<div><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.jobexcel.com/uploads/allimg/130314/1_1228402825.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"288\" border=\"0\" /></div>\nI recently went to a school sports day for 6 to 10 year olds.\nThe teacher introducing the event delivered the message<strong> ‘It’s not about winning, it’s about having fun‘.</strong>\n\nUnfortunately it’s a lie.\n\nThis message is just not accurate. And it stifles everyone’s communication skills. Every kid would like to win. Every parent at the event would like their child to win. The winner gets more satisfaction and glory. In fact, if it wasn’t about winning, there would be no race!\nWe deliver messages like this because we want to spare our children the cut throat pressure that may go with competition. A noble goal. But a goal that won’t be achieved if the children don’t believe what we say.\nHowever, we can easily create a true and accurate message that breaks down the barrier and achieves the intended goal; with just a slight tweak.\n\n‘It’s not just about winning, it’s also about having fun’.\n\nBecause this message states the truth, the audience is still listening to the important point about having fun. This message introduces the day and sets the right tone.\nA true message resonates and creates clear communication. A false message is treated with disdain and encourages duplicity.\nIt’s the same for clear business communication. You can improve your communication skills by modifying your messages.\nWe don’t have to be fake, we just need to think clearly about how the message is received.\nBe Sociable, Share!','Barriers to communication: “Not about winning”','This message is just not accurate. And it stifles everyone’s communication skills. Every kid would like to win. Every parent at the event would like their child to win. The winner gets more satisfaction and glory. In fact, if it wasn’t about winning, there would be no race!\nWe deliver messages like this because we want to spare our children the cut throat pressure that may go with competition. A noble goal. But a goal that won’t be achieved if the children don’t believe what we say.','inherit','open','open','','294-autosave','','','2013-03-26 17:18:32','2013-03-26 09:18:32','',294,'http://hanxianlong.tk/?p=311',0,'revision','',0),(312,1,'2013-01-25 15:51:14','2013-01-25 07:51:14','test<a href=\"http://www.tudou.com/v/LRRPigW1rko/&amp;resourceId=0_04_05_99/v.swf\">aabc</a>','test','','inherit','open','open','','83-revision-3','','','2013-01-25 15:51:14','2013-01-25 07:51:14','',83,'http://mydm.dameitui.com/?p=312',0,'revision','',0),(313,1,'2013-03-28 20:58:05','2013-03-28 12:58:05','','025','','inherit','open','open','','025','','','2013-03-28 20:58:05','2013-03-28 12:58:05','',83,'http://mydm.dameitui.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/025.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(315,1,'2013-03-14 10:29:29','2013-03-14 02:29:29','EPA\r\nExecutive Presentation Academy.\r\n\r\n关于EPA\r\nExecutive Presentation Academy是专业提供各类高端商务演示能力辅导和咨询的研究机构。结合全球顶尖的演讲大师资源，EPA致力于为商界人士提供各类重要场合演讲和信息发布的完整解决方案，包括演示设计、私密辅导及相关专业咨询。\r\n\r\nEPA的专业导师和顾问团队在此领域从事研究和辅导超过30年，以全球第一演讲教练Jerry Weissman领衔的大师顾问团队具有丰富的演示辅导经验和大量的客户成果。Jerry本人在美国辅导了超过500家企业的上市路演演讲设计和高管现场传递。\r\n\r\nCombining theory and practice with over 30 years’ experience, the Executive Presentation Academy(EPA) has been created to offer new programs and consulting services that combine the best master thinking on speaking and persuasion wi<ins datetime=\"2013-03-14T01:53:48+00:00\"></ins><ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<blockquote></blockquote>\r\n\r\nth hard-headed corporate experience of what works-and what doesn’t-in high-stakes corporate presentations. Our premiere courses and services include roadshow design and delivery, executive personal coach, comprehensive workshops and full conference consulting package.  \r\n\r\nWe help great ideas to be perfectly delivered!\r\n\r\n我们提供的服务\r\n\tRoadshow Design & Delivery 路演设计和传递\r\n提供全方位的提案、产品发布、解决方案展示及IPO上市各个类型的路演设计和展示方案实施。\r\n\r\n\r\n\tPersonal Coach 个人专属辅导\r\n提供针对高管层的专属私密一对一演示力辅导，由全球顶尖演示团队根据客户的具体情况和要求量身定做。\r\nAnyone who want further coaching and instruction to continue on their paths to excellence or to prepare for a particular speaking engagement, presentation or speech. We are available to discuss your needs for specialized one-on-one coaching.\r\n\r\n\tComprehensive Workshop Training 演示内训课程\r\n完整全面的全系列演示力内训，从思考力、设计力、表现力等各个方面为企业管理层打造耳目一新的演示内容和富有魅力的演示风格\r\n我们的这一系列高级商务演示课程旨在帮助学员在工作中学会逻辑化及高效思考，并为他们提供一个有力的说服方法。学员们将在跨文化交流的情景设定中，获得最前沿、最有效的商务演示技能。这门课程将逻辑技能和口头表达技能有机结合，非常适合管理层人群学习。\r\n我们将着眼于一系列通过对500强客户的需求调研和学员问题研究所积累的丰富案例，将其贯穿到课程的各个方面。这门课程非常重视与学员的互动，设置了大量的讨论、案例分析和课堂练习。让学员充分掌握有效的演示理念和技术，迅速在高端商务演示中脱颖而出。\r\n\t这一系列课程包括：\r\nPWC: Presenting With Charm-Essential Presentation Delivery\r\nPWI: Presenting With Impact-Conference Room Presentation\r\nPWS: Presenting With Stories-Marketing/Sales Presentations\r\nPWP: Presenting With Power-Ball Room Presentation \r\nPWR: Presenting With Result-Presentation For Executives \r\nPWL: Presenting With Leadership-Leaders Presentation\r\nRoadshow Skills For Financial Analysts-- Buy-side/Sell-side \r\nBOTN: The Back of the Napkin-Presenting Visually \r\n\r\nSample course agenda\r\nPWI课程安排\r\nTopic\t内容\tContent\r\n第一部分：\r\n提升提案思考的质量\t1. 跨越商务提案类演示的常见障碍和误区\r\n2. 优秀演讲者所具备的特色和执行要点\r\n3. 一对多、面对面演示和呈现的独特规律\r\n4. 获得清晰的思路：思维导图、鱼骨图等工具的使用\r\n5. 成功商务提案的流程和结构\t1. Business presentation obstacles\r\n2. Excellent speakers Features and implement points\r\n3. Unique law of One-to-many & face-to-face presentation\r\n4. Clear thinking tools\r\n5. Processes and structures\r\n第二部分：\r\n提升提案现场表现力\t1. 塑造专业感：台上表现6 法则\r\n2. 训练方法：团队和个人的自我训练方法、工具、计划\r\n3. 克服临场的焦虑和紧张感\r\n4. 如何把语言风格变得生动有趣、富有感染力\r\n5. 向听众传递内容的特色和亮点\t1. Professional image: performance 6 rules\r\n2. Training methods\r\n3. Overcome the anxiety and tension\r\n4. Change language style \r\n5. Features and highlights delivery\r\n第三部分：\r\n提案PPT 视觉沟通力\t1. 常见职场 PPT 幻灯片的误区\r\n2. 制作简洁美观PPT 幻灯片的方法技巧\r\n3. PPT 演讲的流程设计、信息设计、页面设计\r\n4. 立体和高效传递信息的方法和工具\r\n5. 来自 500 强的典型PPT 幻灯片分析\r\n6. 现场制作演练\t1. Common misunderstanding\r\n2. Slides created skills\r\n3. PPT presentation process design, information design, pages design\r\n4. Deliver methods and tools\r\n5.Case study: PPT slides from Fortune 500\r\n6. Practice\r\n第四部分：\r\n互动沟通策略\t1. 体验并分析双向沟通的特征和执行难度\r\n2. 管理听众的注意力：商务演讲的心跳法则\r\n3. 与听众互动沟通的技巧方法和执行要点\r\n4. 如何设计并管理听众的反应\r\n5. 如何回应疑难和刁钻的问题\r\n6. 个性化说服风格的解析和测试\t1. Two-way communication features and difficulty\r\n2. Manage audience\'s attention: heartbeat rules\r\n3. The interaction techniques and key points\r\n4. How to design and manage the reaction of the audience\r\n5. How to respond to tough questions\r\n6. The personalized convince style test\r\n第五部分：\r\n商务演讲的策划及情景演练\t1. 演讲和汇报的策划和筹备阶段的方法应用和表现测试\r\n2. 商务演讲中的团队分工合作\r\n3. 台上表现力的执行、观察、解析、交叉点评、总结\r\n4. 检测并提升学员在内容清晰度、肢体语言、说服方法、互动策略、问题应对方面的临场表现并给予改善建议\t1. Performance testing for speech planning stage\r\n2. Teamwork in business presentations\r\n3. Practice and Summarize\r\n4. Summarizing idea techniques\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nConsulting of Conference Presentations 企业会议方案设计和实施\r\n\r\n<div><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.jobexcel.com/uploads/allimg/130314/1_1022307251.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"288\" border=\"0\" />\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n我们的客户\r\n<div><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.jobexcel.com/uploads/allimg/130314/1_1022305472.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"288\" border=\"0\" />\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n','关于我们','','inherit','open','open','','48-revision-10','','','2013-03-14 10:29:29','2013-03-14 02:29:29','',48,'http://mydm.dameitui.com/?p=315',0,'revision','',0),(316,1,'2013-03-14 10:31:43','2013-03-14 02:31:43','','演讲白皮书','','inherit','open','open','','66-revision-3','','','2013-03-14 10:31:43','2013-03-14 02:31:43','',66,'http://mydm.dameitui.com/?p=316',0,'revision','',0),(317,1,'2013-01-28 16:51:56','2013-01-28 08:51:56','<table style=\"border: 0;\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"142\">理念</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"142\">活动</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"142\">嘉宾</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"142\">共建者</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"142\">这是一个分享创见和智识的公益活动，关注并分享不同领域具有开创性、建设性的尝试、经历和成果，旨在“用思考、坚守、创造来感动时代、改变世界”。</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"142\">八月到十月，北京、成都、广州、上海4场思想分享盛会，30余位业界精英，用演讲或表演的形式在16分钟内展现他们的异想天开 ，各场活动视频将通过网络免费共享。</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"142\">他们来自科学、技术、设计、文化、艺术、传媒、社会、商业等领域；他们热衷于自己的专业、有近乎偏执的坚守，推崇自由的精神、但不拘泥于专业领域；他们用非凡的创想与实践重新定义专业的边界；他们将用亲历打动我们、感动时代、改变世界。</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"142\">在这个创造力式微的国度，Think+这个新生儿蹒跚学步。庆幸的是，我们有着众多共建者的鼎力支持，他们与我们一同带着“感动时代、改变世界”的异想天开，艰难上路。</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>','视频集锦','','inherit','open','open','','149-revision-10','','','2013-01-28 16:51:56','2013-01-28 08:51:56','',149,'http://mydm.dameitui.com/?p=317',0,'revision','',0),(318,1,'2013-03-28 21:03:12','2013-03-28 13:03:12','联系咨询的内容，请在此处编辑内容即可。这是联系咨询的内容，请在此处编辑内容即可。这是联系咨询的内容，请在此处编辑内容即可。这是联系咨询的内容，请在此处编辑内容即可。这是联系咨询的内容，请在此处编辑内容即可。这是联系咨询的内容，请在此处编辑内容即可。这是联系咨询的内容，请在此处编辑内容即可。这是联系咨询的内容，请在此处编辑内容即可。这是联系咨询的内容，请在此处编辑内容即可。\r\n<table width=\"683\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align=\"left\" bgcolor=\"#ccc